TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ince, Baris
AU  - Ozsoylev, Han
T1  - Price of Regulations: Regulatory Costs and the Cross-section of Stock Returns
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/raae001
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 14
IS  - 3
SP  - 381
EP  - 427
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - Regulations introduce significant fixed costs and add to operating leverage. Fixed regulatory costs that contribute to operating leverage should generate a risk premium. To explore whether such a premium exists, we introduce a measure of “regulatory operating leverage” that reflects the importance of fixed regulatory costs in a firm’s cost structure. Regulatory operating leverage predicts stock returns in the cross-section, and a zero-cost high-low regulatory operating leverage strategy generates positive and significant risk-adjusted return. Finally, the impact of regulatory operating leverage on returns is due to the (systematic) risk contribution of fixed regulatory costs.
Y2  - 6/6/2025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/raae001
ER  - 



